34#ifdef __NetBSD__
35# define __iomem __nvkm_memory_iomem
36#endif

38/******************************************************************************
39 * instmem object base implementation
40 *****************************************************************************/
41#define nvkm_instobj(p) container_of((p), struct nvkm_instobj, memory)
42
43struct nvkm_instobj {
44 struct nvkm_memory memory;
45 struct nvkm_memory *parent;
46 struct nvkm_instmem *imem;
47 struct list_head head;
48 u32 *suspend;
49 void __iomem *map;
50};
51
52static enum nvkm_memory_target
53nvkm_instobj_target(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
54{
55 memory = nvkm_instobj(memory)->parent;
56 return nvkm_memory_target(memory);
57}
58
59static u64
60nvkm_instobj_addr(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
61{
62 memory = nvkm_instobj(memory)->parent;
63 return nvkm_memory_addr(memory);
64}
65
66static u64
67nvkm_instobj_size(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
68{
69 memory = nvkm_instobj(memory)->parent;
70 return nvkm_memory_size(memory);
71}
72
73static void
74nvkm_instobj_release(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
75{
76 struct nvkm_instobj *iobj = nvkm_instobj(memory);
77 nvkm_bar_flush(iobj->imem->subdev.device->bar);
78}
79
80static void __iomem *
81nvkm_instobj_acquire(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
82{
83 return nvkm_instobj(memory)->map;
84}
85
86#ifdef __NetBSD__
87
88/*
89 * XXX I think this should be done with bus_space, but the depth of
90 * abstractions is dizzying and I'm not actually sure where these
91 * pointers come from.
92 */
93
94# define ioread32_native fake_ioread32_native
95# define iowrite32_native fake_iowrite32_native
96
97static inline uint32_t
98ioread32_native(const void __iomem *ptr)
99{
100 uint32_t v;
101
102 v = *(const uint32_t __iomem *)ptr;
103 membar_consumer();
104
105 return v;
106}
107
108static inline void
109iowrite32_native(uint32_t v, void __iomem *ptr)
110{
111
112 membar_producer();
113 *(uint32_t __iomem *)ptr = v;
114}
115
116#endif
117
118static u32
119nvkm_instobj_rd32(struct nvkm_memory *memory, u64 offset)
120{
121 return ioread32_native((const char *)nvkm_instobj(memory)->map + offset);
122}
123
124static void
125nvkm_instobj_wr32(struct nvkm_memory *memory, u64 offset, u32 data)
126{
127 iowrite32_native(data, (char *)nvkm_instobj(memory)->map + offset);
128}
129
130#ifdef __NetBSD__
131# undef ioread32_native
132# undef iowrite32_native
133#endif
134
135static void
136nvkm_instobj_map(struct nvkm_memory *memory, struct nvkm_vma *vma, u64 offset)
137{
138 memory = nvkm_instobj(memory)->parent;
139 nvkm_memory_map(memory, vma, offset);
140}
141
142static void *
143nvkm_instobj_dtor(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
144{
145 struct nvkm_instobj *iobj = nvkm_instobj(memory);
146 spin_lock(&iobj->imem->lock);
147 list_del(&iobj->head);
148 spin_unlock(&iobj->imem->lock);
149 nvkm_memory_del(&iobj->parent);
150 return iobj;
151}
152
153const struct nvkm_memory_func
154nvkm_instobj_func = {
155 .dtor = nvkm_instobj_dtor,
156 .target = nvkm_instobj_target,
157 .addr = nvkm_instobj_addr,
158 .size = nvkm_instobj_size,
159 .acquire = nvkm_instobj_acquire,
160 .release = nvkm_instobj_release,
161 .rd32 = nvkm_instobj_rd32,
162 .wr32 = nvkm_instobj_wr32,
163 .map = nvkm_instobj_map,
164};
165
166static void
167nvkm_instobj_boot(struct nvkm_memory *memory, struct nvkm_vm *vm)
168{
169 memory = nvkm_instobj(memory)->parent;
170 nvkm_memory_boot(memory, vm);
171}
172
173static void
174nvkm_instobj_release_slow(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
175{
176 struct nvkm_instobj *iobj = nvkm_instobj(memory);
177 nvkm_instobj_release(memory);
178 nvkm_done(iobj->parent);
179}
180
181static void __iomem *
182nvkm_instobj_acquire_slow(struct nvkm_memory *memory)
183{
184 struct nvkm_instobj *iobj = nvkm_instobj(memory);
185 iobj->map = nvkm_kmap(iobj->parent);
186 if (iobj->map)
187 memory->func = &nvkm_instobj_func;
188 return iobj->map;
189}
190
191static u32
192nvkm_instobj_rd32_slow(struct nvkm_memory *memory, u64 offset)
193{
194 struct nvkm_instobj *iobj = nvkm_instobj(memory);
195 return nvkm_ro32(iobj->parent, offset);
196}
197
198static void
199nvkm_instobj_wr32_slow(struct nvkm_memory *memory, u64 offset, u32 data)
200{
201 struct nvkm_instobj *iobj = nvkm_instobj(memory);
202 return nvkm_wo32(iobj->parent, offset, data);
203}
204
205const struct nvkm_memory_func
206nvkm_instobj_func_slow = {
207 .dtor = nvkm_instobj_dtor,
208 .target = nvkm_instobj_target,
209 .addr = nvkm_instobj_addr,
210 .size = nvkm_instobj_size,
211 .boot = nvkm_instobj_boot,
212 .acquire = nvkm_instobj_acquire_slow,
213 .release = nvkm_instobj_release_slow,
214 .rd32 = nvkm_instobj_rd32_slow,
215 .wr32 = nvkm_instobj_wr32_slow,
216 .map = nvkm_instobj_map,
217};
218
219int
220nvkm_instobj_new(struct nvkm_instmem *imem, u32 size, u32 align, bool zero,
221 struct nvkm_memory **pmemory)
222{
223 struct nvkm_memory *memory = NULL;
224 struct nvkm_instobj *iobj;
225 u32 offset;
226 int ret;
227
228 ret = imem->func->memory_new(imem, size, align, zero, &memory);
229 if (ret)
230 goto done;
231
232 if (!imem->func->persistent) {
233 if (!(iobj = kzalloc(sizeof(*iobj), GFP_KERNEL))) {
234 ret = -ENOMEM;
235 goto done;
236 }
237
238 nvkm_memory_ctor(&nvkm_instobj_func_slow, &iobj->memory);
239 iobj->parent = memory;
240 iobj->imem = imem;
241 spin_lock(&iobj->imem->lock);
242 list_add_tail(&iobj->head, &imem->list);
243 spin_unlock(&iobj->imem->lock);
244 memory = &iobj->memory;
245 }
246
247 if (!imem->func->zero && zero) {
248 void __iomem *map = nvkm_kmap(memory);
249 if (unlikely(!map)) {
250 for (offset = 0; offset < size; offset += 4)
251 nvkm_wo32(memory, offset, 0x00000000);
252 } else {
253 memset_io(map, 0x00, size);
254 }
255 nvkm_done(memory);
256 }
257
258done:
259 if (ret)
260 nvkm_memory_del(&memory);
261 *pmemory = memory;
262 return ret;
263}

265/******************************************************************************
266 * instmem subdev base implementation
267 *****************************************************************************/
268
269u32
270nvkm_instmem_rd32(struct nvkm_instmem *imem, u32 addr)
271{
272 return imem->func->rd32(imem, addr);
273}
274
275void
276nvkm_instmem_wr32(struct nvkm_instmem *imem, u32 addr, u32 data)
277{
278 return imem->func->wr32(imem, addr, data);
279}
280
281static int
282nvkm_instmem_fini(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev, bool suspend)
283{
284 struct nvkm_instmem *imem = nvkm_instmem(subdev);
285 struct nvkm_instobj *iobj;
286 int i;
287
288 if (imem->func->fini)
289 imem->func->fini(imem);
290
291 if (suspend) {
292 list_for_each_entry(iobj, &imem->list, head) {
293 struct nvkm_memory *memory = iobj->parent;
294 u64 size = nvkm_memory_size(memory);
295
296 iobj->suspend = vmalloc(size);
297 if (!iobj->suspend)
298 return -ENOMEM;
299
300 for (i = 0; i < size; i += 4)
301 iobj->suspend[i / 4] = nvkm_ro32(memory, i);
302 }
303 }
304
305 return 0;
306}
307
308static int
309nvkm_instmem_oneinit(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
310{
311 struct nvkm_instmem *imem = nvkm_instmem(subdev);
312 if (imem->func->oneinit)
313 return imem->func->oneinit(imem);
314 return 0;
315}
316
317static int
318nvkm_instmem_init(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
319{
320 struct nvkm_instmem *imem = nvkm_instmem(subdev);
321 struct nvkm_instobj *iobj;
322 int i;
323
324 list_for_each_entry(iobj, &imem->list, head) {
325 if (iobj->suspend) {
326 struct nvkm_memory *memory = iobj->parent;
327 u64 size = nvkm_memory_size(memory);
328 for (i = 0; i < size; i += 4)
329 nvkm_wo32(memory, i, iobj->suspend[i / 4]);
330 vfree(iobj->suspend);
331 iobj->suspend = NULL;
332 }
333 }
334
335 return 0;
336}
337
338static void *
339nvkm_instmem_dtor(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
340{
341 struct nvkm_instmem *imem = nvkm_instmem(subdev);
342 if (imem->func->dtor)
343 return imem->func->dtor(imem);
344 return imem;
345}
346
347static const struct nvkm_subdev_func
348nvkm_instmem = {
349 .dtor = nvkm_instmem_dtor,
350 .oneinit = nvkm_instmem_oneinit,
351 .init = nvkm_instmem_init,
352 .fini = nvkm_instmem_fini,
353};
354
355void
356nvkm_instmem_ctor(const struct nvkm_instmem_func *func,
357 struct nvkm_device *device, int index,
358 struct nvkm_instmem *imem)
359{
360 nvkm_subdev_ctor(&nvkm_instmem, device, index, 0, &imem->subdev);
361 imem->func = func;
362 spin_lock_init(&imem->lock);
363 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&imem->list);
364}
